del 4. Sex was coded with female as reference. Former and current smoker were coded with non-", "bbox": [57.8, 701.0, 730.0, 712.1]}, {"text": "smoker as reference. Regular alcohol intake was coded with non-drinker as reference. Hypertension, diabetes, and stroke were coded with no respective health condition", "bbox": [57.8, 711.7, 730.1, 722.8]}, {"text": "experienced for the last 12 months as reference. Model statistics were based on the ﬁrst imputed dataset.", "bbox": [57.8, 721.1, 482.2, 733.5]}, {"text": "† p < 0.10.", "bbox": [57.8, 731.6, 100.0, 744.2]}, {"text": "* p < 0.05.", "bbox": [57.8, 743.8, 99.7, 754.9]}, {"text": "** p < 0.001.", "bbox": [57.8, 754.5, 107.8, 765.6]}, {"text": "Waist-to-hip ratio", "bbox": [235.9, 780.7, 358.1, 798.3]}, {"text": "Our models for the effect of WHR on episodic memory and executive functions are", "bbox": [235.9, 803.4, 704.1, 818.6]}, {"text": "summarized in Table 4. Similar with BMI, we observed that WHR was negatively", "bbox": [235.9, 822.2, 691.0, 837.5]}, {"text": "associated with episodic memory after controlling for demographic variables in the", "bbox": [235.9, 841.1, 699.7, 856.4]}, {"text": "ﬁrst model (B = -0.657, SE = 0.179, 95% CI [-1.009, -0.305], p < 0.001). However,", "bbox": [235.9, 857.7, 701.0, 875.8]}, {"text": "in contrast to BMI, WHR remained a signiﬁcant predictor of episodic memory after", "bbox": [235.9, 877.0, 706.1, 894.1]}, {"text": "we included health status and health behaviors as covariates in the second model", "bbox": [235.9, 897.7, 689.0, 913.0]}, {"text": "Hartanto and Yong (2018), PeerJ, DOI 10.7717/peerj.5624 10/20", "bbox": [42.7, 944.5, 730.0, 957.7]}]}